          <p>Effective Date: <b>2023-03-28 05:20:54 PM</b></p>
          <p>This Cookie Policy explains how Abro Egypt ("we", "us", or "our") uses cookies and similar technologies to collect and store information when you use our website. By using our website, you consent to our use of cookies in accordance with this policy.</p>
          <h2>1. What are cookies?</h2>
          <p>Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device (such as your computer or mobile device) when you visit a website. Cookies help us to recognize your device and remember information about your visit, such as your preferences, and enable certain website features.</p>
          <h2>2. Types of Cookies We Use:</h2>
          <p>We use both session cookies and persistent cookies on our website.</p>
          <p>Session cookies are temporary cookies that are deleted when you close your browser or log out of your account. We use session cookies to provide certain website features, such as enabling you to access secure areas of our website.</p>
          <p>Persistent cookies remain on your device even after you close your browser or log out of your account. We use persistent cookies to remember your preferences and provide you with a personalized experience when you return to our website.</p>
          <p>We also use third-party cookies, which are cookies placed by third-party service providers to help us analyze website usage and improve our website. We do not control these cookies and have no access to the information they collect. You should review the third-party service provider's privacy policy for more information on how they use cookies.</p>
          <p>The cookies we use on our website include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Strictly necessary cookies: These cookies are essential for the operation of our website and enable you to use its features. Without these cookies, you may not be able to use certain website features.</li>
            <li>Performance cookies: These cookies collect information about how visitors use our website, such as which pages are most popular and how long visitors spend on each page. We use this information to improve our website and optimize its performance.</li>
            <li>Functionality cookies: These cookies remember your preferences and enable certain website features, such as providing personalized content and remembering your language preferences.</li>
            <li>Targeting cookies: These cookies are used to deliver personalized advertisements to you based on your browsing history and interests. We may use third-party advertising partners to display these advertisements.</li>
          </ul>
          <h2>3. How to Control Cookies:</h2>
          <p>You can control and manage cookies through your browser settings. Most browsers allow you to block or delete cookies, as well as to manage your cookie preferences. Please note that if you choose to block cookies, you may not be able to use certain website features or access certain content.</p>
          <h2>4. Changes to this Cookie Policy:</h2>
          <p>We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our cookie practices or applicable laws. We encourage you to review this policy periodically for any updates or changes.</p>
          <h2>5. Contact Us:</h2>
          <p>If you have any questions or concerns about our use of cookies, please contact us at <a href="mailto:info@abroegypt.com">info@abroegypt.com</a>.</p>
